alsop, 41, says he will use the portable phone to keep in touch with the media along the way of his trek from the berkshires to boston to draw attention to massachusetts' water resources
i think it's wonderful that in the midst of one of the most densely populated states in the nation, by focusing on an idea and an element in the environment, i can go and have a great adventure,'' alsop told the three dozen environmentalists, schoolchildren and others gathered at the launch site monday
the 33-day trip, sponsored by the massachusetts audubon society, includes a planned stop at walden pond near concord, where the famed 19th century writer henry david thoreau lived in an isolated cabin for more than two years
