lehr, a democrat, defeated republican john ashcroft, now missouri's governor, for state auditor in 1974. lehr was mentioned as a candidate for the democratic nomination for governor in 1976, but made the surprise announcement that he was resigning as auditor and leaving politics
he became president of the empire bank and trust co. in kansas city and later became chairman and chief executive officer of traders bank there
lehr accepted the pension fund job in 1981 and worked with the u.s. labor department to clean it up. the fund allegedly had been under mob control. two years ago, the general accounting office said the fund was being run properly for the first time in its 30 years
hester r. mccullough, once a heroine of the political right for her 1940s stand against entertainers associated with communist causes, died sunday at age 71
