some stocks also were boosted by rumored and actual takeovers, reflecting a stunning increase in merger activity over the past several weeks
nevertheless, stockbrokers said the relatively low volume of trading and the lack of any significant economic signals showed that many investors remain reluctant to re-enter the market in the aftermath of the october crash
people still are wounded,'' said philip c. puccio, manager of institutional trading at dillon read &amp; co. ``those wounds have not scarred over yet. there's fear we could be looking at another downdraft.''
lucky stores was the most active issue, jumping 14] to 46| in heavy trading after rival chain american stores announced a $45-a-share tender offer for the company
