we're right on the top of the fence and don't know which way we're going to fall,'' said robert o'toole, manager of over-the-counter trading at shearson lehman hutton inc. in new york. ``it's very slow. the only thing good is that when the market's down, volume dries up. that indicates there's not much selling.''
